===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
The character derives from its proto-form [[悤]], which represents a heart/mind (心) with a big dot on top indicating a hole. According to Qiu Xigui (裘錫圭) and Shen Pei (沈培), it indicates an open heart and an open mind. Its original meaning was "intelligent". Later, it became {{Han compound|囪|心|c1=p|c2=s|t2=heart|ls=psc}}, hence the dot on top became the pictogram of a window.

Eventually, the character evolved into 聰, i.e., {{Han compound|耳|悤|c1=s|c2=p|t1=ear|ls=psc}}, in which the ear symbolizes somebody willing to listen and learn fastly through hearing.

